main event: An object was observed for more than one hour at Lake Andes, South Dakota on January 30, 1956.
interesting points: The report concluded that the sighting was generated by a weather balloon, probably of the radiosonde type., The object was still in sight when the report was submitted., The reporting officer indicated there was no discernible flight path or maneuvers., There were civilian witnesses observing the construction of a water tower during the sighting., The weather conditions were clear and cold at the time of the observation.
sighted object: weather balloon, possibly of radiosonde type
